ppunctuations.ppunctuation:
Executed: not quite regularly.
Usage: not always logical.
Dividers:
I. Colon.
II. Four dot asterisk (e.g. fols.: 6v, l.5; 9v, ls. 5, 7; 11v, l.1; 34v, l.1; 35r; ls. 6, 7, 11);  
nine dot asterisk (used throughout the text);
doubled nine dot asterisks (esp. fol. 25v, l.1);
doubled four dot asterisks (esp. fol. 35r, l.13).

rubrications.rubrication:
Nomina sacra; 
the first and the second line in the incipit page (fol. 3r);
some lines (one, two) at paragraph beginning on fols. 4r (ls. 15-16), 17r (ls. 4-5), 17v (l.5), 22v (ls. 17-18), 25v (ls. 2-3);
the horizontal dashes above and below Ethiopic numerals; 
elements of the punctuation signs;
names of the donors.
